derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English deynseyn, via Anglo-Norman French from Old French deinz 'within' (from Latin de 'from' + intus 'within') + -ein (from Latin -aneus '-aneous'). The change in the form of the word was due to association with citizen

entry.tran: (某一特定地方的)居民，动物，植物
entry.def: A denizen of a particular place is a person, animal, or plant that lives or grows in this place.
